ical conditions shown by our short-term study, suggest that this method weakens thermal stratification, enhancing nutrient inputs from hypolimnic waters causing elevated phytoplankton biomass and primary production in metalimnetic and epilimnetic layers shifting the overall metabolic balance of the water column toward net autotrophy. On the other hand, biodegradation processes in higher temperature and intensive sinking of organic matter to the sediment and then removing by pipe directly to the outflow, reduce significantly phytoplankton biomass in the hypolimnion of experimental part of the lake.},
author = {Dunalska, Julita A. and Staehr, Peter A. and Jaworska, Bo{\.{z}}ena and G{\'{o}}rniak, Dorota and Gomu{\l}ka, Piotr},
doi = {10.1016/J.ECOLENG.2014.09.048},
