. Our results indicate that the ratio of$\backslash$nthe grazing mortality of the large size category to that of the small$\backslash$nsize category best explains the variation of NBSS slopes across$\backslash$nenvironments, suggesting that higher grazing mortality of large$\backslash$nmicrophytoplankton may release the small phytoplankton from grazing,$\backslash$nwhich in turn leads to a steeper NBSS slope. This study contributes to$\backslash$nunderstanding the relative importance of bottom-up versus top-down$\backslash$ncontrol in shaping microphytoplankton size structure.},
